<section id="overview">
<h2>OLSP Academy Overview &amp; Pricing</h2>
<p>OLSP Academy sits inside the wider "OLSP System," created by online marketer Wayne Crowe, who has been publicly associated with the brand since around 2020. The Academy is the training and onboarding layer: short video lessons, live calls, and a community space, paired with done-for-you marketing pages members can promote.</p>

<h3>What's Included</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Mega Link:</strong> a single trackable referral link members share instead of building their own website or sales page.</li>
<li><strong>Mega Funnel:</strong> a pre-built, automated funnel that follows up with leads who click the Mega Link.</li>
<li><strong>Bootcamp training modules:</strong> beginner lessons covering account setup, link sharing, and basic traffic methods.</li>
<li><strong>Live webinars and Facebook group:</strong> recurring training sessions and a community space for members.</li>
<li><strong>Optional add-ons:</strong> "Accelerator" coaching, "TD Pages" for building landing pages, and a paid "VIP" tier with extended training and higher commission rates.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Reported Pricing</h3>
<Callout type="warn">
<strong>Pricing caution:</strong> Public sources disagree on current pricing, and "make money online" funnels frequently change their offers and limited-time discounts. Treat the figures below as a general guide drawn from publicly available pages, not a confirmed current price list.
</Callout>
<div class="table-scroll">
<table>
<tr><th>Tier</th><th>Reported Cost</th><th>What It Reportedly Adds</th></tr>
<tr><td>Foundation / Free</td><td>$0</td><td>Basic dashboard, Mega Link, entry-level training, modest commission rate (often cited around 10% on some products)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Entry / launch offer</td><td>Reported as low as $7 in some promotions</td><td>Used as a low-friction first purchase in some marketing pages</td></tr>
<tr><td>VIP / Accelerator</td><td>Reported around $97/month in one third-party review, with one-time VIP commission payouts cited as $150–$300</td><td>Extended coaching, higher commission tiers, additional done-for-you assets</td></tr>
<tr><td>Other upsells (TD Pages, traffic packages)</td><td>Varies; not consistently reported</td><td>Landing-page builder, paid traffic packages such as solo ads</td></tr>
</table>
</div>
<p><strong>Target audience:</strong> Marketing copy positions OLSP Academy at total beginners with "zero tech skills." In practice, anyone evaluating it should be comfortable with the idea that most of the realistic earning paths involve getting other people to join and upgrade — not selling a tangible product to a one-time customer.</p>
</section>

<section id="design">
<h2>Platform &amp; Build Quality</h2>
<p>We did not get hands-on access to the member dashboard, so we cannot describe its interface first-hand. Based on third-party walkthroughs, the public description is consistent: a single dashboard houses training modules, the Mega Link, performance tracking, and links to community channels.</p>

<h3>Visual Appeal &amp; Trust Signals</h3>
<p>One promotional landing page we checked (theolspacademy.com) still carried default placeholder metadata from the website-building tool used to create it, rather than fully customized branding. That is not proof of anything sinister on its own, but it is the kind of detail a careful buyer should notice — it suggests at least one OLSP-branded page online may be a quickly assembled or unofficial copy rather than a fully maintained corporate site.</p>

<h3>Long-Term Considerations</h3>
<p>Done-for-you funnel systems like this one depend on the parent company continuing to maintain the funnel, the community, and the commission structure. If OLSP changes its compensation plan, retires a tool, or shuts down, members lose the system they were trained to depend on — a structural risk shared by most single-vendor "earn inside our ecosystem" platforms.</p>
</section>

<section id="performance">
<h2>Performance Analysis</h2>

<h3>4.1 Core Functionality: How the Mega Link Actually Earns Money</h3>
<p>The core mechanic is simple to describe: a member shares their Mega Link, interested people click it and enter the OLSP funnel, and OLSP's own emails, webinars, and Facebook Lives do the selling. The referring member earns a commission when that person buys an add-on — not necessarily when they simply join for free.</p>

