<section id="faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<FaqItem question="Is OLSP Academy a scam?">
<p>We found no evidence in our research that OLSP Academy is fraudulent or illegal. It is best understood as a recruitment-driven affiliate marketing program — a legitimate but high-promotion business model where results depend heavily on referring new paying members. That is different from being a scam, but it carries different risks than selling a standalone product directly.</p>
</FaqItem>
<FaqItem question="Is it really free to join?">
<p>Multiple sources describe a free entry tier, with paid upsells for VIP coaching, landing pages, and traffic packages. We could not independently confirm current pricing at the time of writing — verify directly on the official sign-up page before assuming any price.</p>
</FaqItem>
<FaqItem question="Who is Wayne Crowe?">
<p>Wayne Crowe is the individual most consistently credited as the creator of the OLSP System, describing himself publicly as having worked in online marketing for around 15 years. One source attributed the system to a different person, which we could not reconcile.</p>
</FaqItem>
<FaqItem question="Can a complete beginner realistically earn money with this?">
<p>It's possible, but we have no independently verified data on what a typical beginner actually earns. Self-reported progress videos exist publicly, but they are not audited and likely overrepresent successful members, which is common across this category of program.</p>
</FaqItem>
